\ Problem 1
\ If we list all the natural numbers below 10 that are multiples of 3 or 5, we 
\ get 3, 5, 6 and 9. The sum of these multiples is 23. Find the sum of all the 
\ multiples of 3 or 5 below 1000.

\ is n a multiple of k?
: multiple ( n k --)
	mod 0= ;

\ is n a multiple of 3 or 5?
: 3-or-5 ( n -- f)
	dup 3 multiple swap 5 multiple or ;

\ if n isn't a multiple of 3 or 5, change it to zero
: filter ( n -- n | 0)
	dup 3-or-5 and ;

: maybe-add ( n x -- n + {0 | x})
	filter + ;

: main ( --)
	1000 3 do i maybe-add loop ;

main .
